## Re-fetch protocol

```
1. At session start, the orchestrator checks last_fetched_at for each library.
2. If days_since > library_freshness_threshold_days:
   a. Log warning to tracking/sessions/<id>/observations.jsonl.
   b. Trigger context7.fetch (primary) → fetch (fallback) for that library.
   c. Replace library_docs/<lib>/<version>/ with fresh content.
   d. Update last_fetched_at in this MANIFEST.
   e. Diff old vs new docs; surface API breaking changes via tracking/errors_catalog.json (AIE-004) if any.
3. Log all updates to tracking/sessions/<id>/library_doc_updates.jsonl.
```

## Offline-mode behaviour

If network unavailable:
- Skip re-fetch.
- Log to `library_docs/OFFLINE.md` with timestamp + libraries with stale docs.
- Continue session with existing docs.
- Surface at next HITL gate.

